<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Zixt</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-15 21:21:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I Know for sure that Spirit wolf doesnt work, i'm a human necromancer, and i'm dubious or indiff wiht most high elves but the friggin three that give the quest, which i happen to be KOS.  I do not know if the invis trick works, i think it might, but i'll have to see.  There is another alternative, in Cazic Thule (near ferrott) a Clay golem spawns and drops a "clay ball" as his common drop, this casts illusion:earth elemental.  You are then INDIFF to everything but guards.  So just wait for the guard to walk away, use the potion, walk up to the NPC's and do the quest.  You need three because you lose the form each time you zone.  The clay golem spawns in the maze, not sure where, but he's random.  best way to find it is have a group pulling from the maze.  the priest of najena is a 50 minute spawn up the stairs on the opposite end of the hall near the reclusive ghoul magi in unrest.  Most times its a ghoul, but if ya see him its a 50% drop on the key.  And its a No drop, tarnished brass key i believe.  then go to najena, use one potion, get a note, head to felwithe, use another potion, get a worn cloak, head to erudin enchanters guild, use the last potion and get ur mystic cloak and have fun.  its very tricky using the potion, they are very touchy, dont even worry about hailing them, just give your stuff and get out of there, dont risk hanging around.<BR>
<BR>
Zixt Arathorn<BR>
50th Necromancer<BR>
The Tribunal</font></td></tr></table>
